div.head:
136. Circular Telegram From the Department of
                            State to Certain Diplomatic and Consular
                            MissionsSource:
                            Department of State, Central Files, 394.41/11–760. Confidential;
                            Priority; Verbatim Text. Drafted by Michael J. Dux, of the Trade
                            Agreements Division of the Office of International Trade, on November 4;
                            cleared by Hadraba and Martin and
                            in substance by BNA, WE, and FE;
                            and initialed for the Acting Secretary by Martin. Sent to London, Rome,
                            Brussels, Paris, The Hague, Tokyo, and Geneva.
